<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>New Campground</title>
</head>
<body>
    <form action="/campgrounds" method="POST">
        <div>
            <label for="title">Title:</label>
            <input type="text" id="title" name="campground[title]"> <!-- "campground[title]" : In request's body (payload), this will be as 'req.body.campground.title'  (This is a nice thing to do) We're gonna group things under "campground". when our data is sent via POST request, to our express app - to the server; everyting in the 'req.body' will be stored under campground. -->
        </div>
        <div>
            <label for="location">Location:</label>
            <input type="text" id="location" name="campground[location]">
        </div>
        <button>Submit (Add campground)</button>        
    </form>
    <a href="/campgrounds">All Campgrounds</a>
    
</body>
</html>